@node "INSTALL" "SN Bulletins v2.1 - Installation Procedures"
@toc "MAIN"
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN Bulletins v2.1 - Installation Procedures
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

 1  Run the included installation script either of the following
    two ways:

    a.  Type "Installer Install_Bulletins" from the Shell.

    b.  Click on the "Install_Bulletins" icon from Workbench.

 2  The installation script moves the required files to your specified
    location and creates an environment variable pointing to the directory
    above it.

 3  Add "{#4PFiles:Bulls/SN_Bulletins %23}" to your sys.welcome (or your
    _Begin/_End/_Added files if you're using SN LoginConfig) if you wish to
    display the Bulletins Menu at login.  Otherwise, just do the next step.

 4  Add "BM |{#4PFiles:Bulls/SN_Bulletins %23}" to your bbsmenu (and add
    the option to your main menu) so users can view the Bulletins Menu at
    any time.

    Note that the above {'s in 3 & 4 are actually control-Q commands and
    be sure to modify the paths to reflect your setup!

 5  Using your favorite text editor, load up the file "_Bulls" and edit
    it according to your needs.  The format of the file is as follows:

    SN:Bulls/Rules            Path/filename of the text file.
    Rules and Regulations     Title users will see in BM.

 6  Reload your bbstext/bbsmenu via CNet's Control Panel menu (option
    #3, "Text/menu reload  RAmiga-T" and you're all set!

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
@node "BUGS" "SN Bulletins v2.1 - Bugs/Problems"
@toc "MAIN"
┌───────────────────────────────────┐
  SN Bulletins v2.1 - Bugs/Problems
└───────────────────────────────────┘

  - No known bugs at this point.  This has been in operation for at least
    four years now, probably a little more.  Except for some code clean-up,
    nothing has really changed, so it should be very stable.  I've never
    had any problems with it.  If you see anything fishy, let me know!

    Thanks!

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
